<article class="cf">
    <div class="fl w-100 w-70-l bg-near-white tc">

        <!-- The stats block at the top -->
        <article class="pa3 pa5-ns" data-name="slab-stat">
            <h1>Kaiser in code</h1>
            <dl class="dib mr5">
                <dd class="f6 f5-ns b ml0">Total Commits</dd>
                <dd class="f3 f2-ns b ml0"><%= @info[:commits].count %></dd>
            </dl>
            <dl class="dib mr5">
                <dd class="f6 f5-ns b ml0">Stars</dd>
                <dd class="f3 f2-ns b ml0"><%= @info[:repos].sum(:stars) %></dd>
            </dl>
            <dl class="dib mr5">
                <dd class="f6 f5-ns b ml0">Most Recent Activity</dd>
                <dd class="f3 f2-ns b ml0"><%= pretty_date @info[:commits].first[:created_at] %></dd>
            </dl>
            <dl class="dib mr5">
                <dd class="f6 f5-ns b ml0">Repo Count</dd>
                <dd class="f3 f2-ns b ml0"><%= @info[:repos].count %></dd>
            </dl>
            <dl class="dib">
                <dd class="f6 f5-ns b ml0">Most Used Languages</dd>
                <dd class="f3 f2-ns b ml0">Go, C++, Ruby</dd>
            </dl>
        </article>

        <h1 class="fw6 f3 lh-copy mt3">
            My Favorite Projects
        </h1>
        <!-- The projects section -->
        <section class="cf">
            <div class="fl w-100 w-33-l bg-near-white tc ph1">
                <article class="mw6 center bg-white br3 pa3 pa4-ns mv3 ba b--black-10">
                    <div class="tc">
                        <img src="../images/mini_c_compiler.png" class="h4 w4 dib" title="Mini C Compiler">
                        <h1 class="f4">Mini C Compiler</h1>
                        <hr class="mw3 bb bw1 b--black-10">
                    </div>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        A compiler for a subset of the C language.
                        It was developed as part of a course at the University of Edinburgh.
                        The project was written almost entirely in Java, and outputs a MIPS file which can be run in the MARS emulator.

                        This is one of the coolest projects I have accomplished, and in particular I enjoyed the connections we made to the linguistic side of Computer Science. 
                        As a result of this project, I am now pursuing research in PL.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f5 black-70">
                        This project must remain private for academic reasons, however if you are interested, shoot me an email: pisterk@gmail.com
                    </p>
                </article>
            </div>
            <div class="fl w-100 w-33-l bg-near-white tc ph1">
                <article class="mw6 center bg-white br3 pa3 pa4-ns mv3 ba b--black-10">
                    <div class="tc">
                        <img src="../images/graphics.png" class="h4 w4 dib" title="Graphics">
                        <h1 class="f4">Graphics Projects</h1>
                        <hr class="mw3 bb bw1 b--black-10">
                    </div>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        At UCSD, I have developed multiple graphics projects including:
                    </p>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        A recursive raytracer. Using 3D object files and scene lighting, I render beautiful images in almost lifelike quality.
                        I originally wrote this in C++, but am in the process of porting it to Go to further improve performance.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        A progressive mesh viewer. After reading in .off files, I render in real time a 3D mesh.
                        The user can interact with the mesh through normal transformation as well as mesh decimation and progression.
                    </p>
                    <br>
                </article> 
            </div>
            <div class="fl w-100 w-33-l bg-near-white tc ph1">
                <article class="mw6 center bg-white br3 pa3 pa4-ns mv3 ba b--black-10">
                    <div class="tc">
                        <img src="../images/ruby_front.png" class="h4 w4 dib" title="Ruby">
                        <h1 class="f4">Ethnio and Ruby</h1>
                        <hr class="mw3 bb bw1 b--black-10">
                    </div>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        Working as a Junior Ruby on Rails Engineer at Ethnio was an eye-opening experience.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        As one of six members in the company, I operated in many parts of the app.
                        By the end, I worked on improving security, 
                        managing and acquiring engagement statistics, 
                        updating old code and libraries, 
                        migrating to a new webserver, 
                        and working with the CEO to design new features.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lh-copy measure center f4 black-70">
                        I learned a lot of valuable lessons, and used much of that knowledge creating this website!
                    </p>
                </article> 
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>

    <!-- The commit history section -->
    <div class="fl w-100 w-30-l bg-near-white tc">
        <h1 class="fw6 f3 lh-copy mt3">
            Recent Commits
        </h1>
        <div class="pa3">
        <div class="overflow-auto">
        <table class="f6 w-100 mw6 center" cellspacing="0" align="center">
            <thead>
            <tr class="stripe-dark">
                <th class="fw6 tc pa3 bg-white">Repo</th>
                <th class="fw6 tc pa3 bg-white">Message</th>
                <th class="fw6 tc pa3 bg-white">Date</th>
                <th class="fw6 tc pa3 bg-white">Sha</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="lh-copy">
                <% @info[:commits].where(author: 'Kaiser Pister').limit(50).each do |commit| %>
                    <tr class="stripe-dark">
                        <td class="pa3"><%= @info[:repos].first(id: commit[:repo_id])[:name] %></td>
                        <td class="pa3"><%= (commit[:message].length > 30) ? commit[:message][0,27] + "..." : commit[:message] %></td>
                        <td class="pa1"><%= pretty_date commit[:created_at] %></td>
                        <td class="pa3">
                            <a href=<%="https://github.com/kpister/#{@info[:repos].first(id: commit[:repo_id])[:name]}/commit/#{commit[:sha]}"%> target="_blank"><%= commit[:sha][0,7] %></a> 
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                <%end%>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</article>

